dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 08 Sep 2023 16:59:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694192367</ingested><modified> 2023-09-08T16:59:31+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Military & Defense]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="2272" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/a4c070d0-4e66-11ee-b7f8-0cafa9e8c923" width="3758"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2272" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/a4c070d0-4e66-11ee-b7f8-0cafa9e8c923" width="3758"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lisi Niesner / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A Ukrainian serviceman stands next to a vehicle that carries a Starlink satellite internet system near the frontline, as Russia's attack on Ukraine continues, in Donetsk region, Ukraine February 27, 2023. REUTERS/Lisi Niesner]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[UKRAINE-CRISIS/DONETSK]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists may have a solution to the International Space Station's fungus problem]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>国际空间站水回收系统中的堵塞物严重堵塞，以至于必须将软管送回地球进行清洁和翻新。这要归功于生物膜的形成：一种相互粘附的微生物群落，通常也粘附在表面上，例如水回收管的内部。这些微生物或真菌的生长会堵塞水处理系统中的过滤器，并使宇航员生病。</p><p>所以太空和地球一样，也存在细菌问题——那又怎样呢？由于生物膜会损害设备的完整性并损坏设备，包括宇航服、回收装置、散热器和水处理设施，因此航天机构可能会花费大量资金来更换受影响的材料。 2023 年全年，NASA 已投入高达<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/atoms/files/fy23_nasa_budget_request_summary.pdf">13 亿美元</a>的预算，用于向国际空间站的货运任务补给。在密闭太空任务中防止微生物生长对于前往月球或火星等地方的长途旅行尤其重要，因为在这些地方快速返回地球进行维修或治疗生病的宇航员不太可行。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在科罗拉多大学、麻省理工学院和美国宇航局艾姆斯研究中心的研究人员之间的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Nature Research;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c6c965be-a8ea-473d-89f4-9754f2675a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Nature+Research&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjNmM5NjViZS1hOGVhLTQ3M2QtODlmNC05NzU0ZjI2NzVhNjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmF0dXJlLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zNDE1MjYtMDIzLTAwMzE2LXciLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjgxN2M2OWY1LWJhNTAtNGI3NS1iMjgzLTRiZTc5MjRiNjc2OSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAX2dslo_VrZNSDt-PIG2OsDNrJlp7BwneIVM6FTP1XDO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41526-023-00316-w" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41526-023-00316-w">交叉合作</a>中，研究人员使用一种特定且众所周知的革兰氏阴性细菌研究了来自空间站的样本。科学家们还与<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://liquiglide.com/">LiquiGlide</a>的专家联手，LiquiGlide 是一家由麻省理工学院研究员 Kripa Varanasi 经营的公司，专门研究“消除固体和液体之间的摩擦”。这项多学科研究发现，在暴露于国际空间站的样本上覆盖一薄层核酸可以防止细菌生长。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/cd90d060-4e64-11ee-b44b-b5c626752eb7" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/cd90d060-4e64-11ee-b44b-b5c626752eb7" style="height:600px;width:900px;" alt="这些小瓶内部是含有新表面材料和微生物的室。它们在静止状态下被发射到国际空间站，以避免在达到微重力条件之前细菌生长。到达国际空间站后，宇航员通过组合小瓶中的各个腔室来激活样本。" data-uuid="8289839e-0b38-3fde-b47f-a7902aed9da2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">太空生物膜计划</div></figure><p>科学家们得出的结论是，这些酸带有轻微的负电荷，可以阻止微生物粘附在表面。但值得注意的是，细菌面临着独特的物理屏障和化学屏障：测试表面被蚀刻成“纳米草”。这些硅尖就像一片小森林，然后用硅油润滑，形成生物膜难以粘附的光滑表面。<br><br>应用这种用核酸覆盖表面以防止生物膜积聚的特定方法表明，在陆地样本中，微生物形成减少了约 74%。令人惊讶的是，空间站样本显示出更大幅度的减少，约 86%。然而，根据这些初步结果，该团队提出的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://news.mit.edu/2023/preventing-biofilms-space-0907">一项建议</a>是，应该在未来的任务中进行更长时间的测试。参与这项研究的科罗拉多大学微生物学专家帕梅拉·弗洛雷斯在一份<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://news.mit.edu/2023/preventing-biofilms-space-0907">声明</a>中表示，“我们不知道它能够保持这种表现多久”。 “因此，我们绝对建议更长的孵化时间，并且如果可能的话，进行连续分析，而不仅仅是终点分析。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/scientists-may-have-a-solution-to-the-international-space-stations-fungus-problem-164725021.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/scientists-may-have-a-solution-to-the-international-space-stations-fungus-problem-164725021.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 817c69f5-ba50-4b75-b283-4be7924b6769</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 08 Sep 2023 16:47:25 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694191645</ingested><modified> 2023-09-08T16:47:30+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nature & Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="3712" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/2edbfda0-4e55-11ee-87df-71a2bbe6eefd" width="5568"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3712" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/2edbfda0-4e55-11ee-87df-71a2bbe6eefd" width="5568"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Four main components on the Roscosmos segment of the International Space Station are pictured as the orbital outpost soared 265 miles above a cloudy Pacific Ocean. From top to bottom, are the Nauka multipurpose laboratory module, the European robotic arm attached to Nauka, the Prichal docking module, and the Soyuz MS-23 crew ship.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[International space station]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Android phones for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>与苹果 iPhone 是 iOS 生态系统中唯一的游戏不同，Android 手机市场的最大优点之一是有多种不同的设备和制造商可供选择。也就是说，当真正需要升级时，丰富的选择可能会让您选择合适的手机变得更加困难。如果您正在寻找一部新手机，但不知道从哪里开始，我们会为您精选适合各种预算的最佳 Android 手机。</p><h2>购买新的 Android 手机需要注意什么</h2><h3>表现</h3><p>当谈到挑选我们最喜欢的 Android 手机时，我们寻找的主要因素非常简单：良好的性能（计算和人工智能）、漂亮的显示屏、坚固的设计、锋利的相机、长电池寿命以及对持续软件支持的重大承诺。对于性能，我们不仅会查看基准测试和其他指标，还会根据响应能力来评估手机。无论您是在阅读、发短信、浏览社交媒体还是玩游戏，没有人想要一台感觉迟缓的设备。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3>展示</h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/54f98de0-a87e-11ed-afd1-54c1e8d571fc" alt="虽然规格与去年相比没有太大变化，但三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra 的 6.8 英寸 120Hz AMOLED 显示屏仍然是市场上最好的智能手机屏幕之一。" data-uuid="f90b4b62-0619-3c10-8a7b-abccc2d7e842"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">萨姆·卢瑟福/Engadget</div></figure><p>在显示器方面，我们通常更喜欢能够产生丰富、饱和的色彩且亮度至少为 600 尼特的 OLED 面板，尽管我们的许多顶级中端和高端手机的亮度都可以达到 1,000 尼特或更高。最近，我们最喜欢的大多数设备还支持 90Hz 或 120Hz 快速刷新率的屏幕，这增加了额外的平滑度和流动性。</p><h3>设计</h3><p>现在我们承认，在决定哪些手机看起来最好时存在一些主观性，但还有其他设计方面，例如防尘防水或屏幕耐用性，可以对长期生存产生很大影响。考虑对无线充电、电源共享（又称反向无线充电）和 UWB 连接的支持等因素也很重要，这些因素可能会影响手机与其他设备的交互方式。</p><h3>相机</h3><p>显然，对于照片，我们希望在明亮和弱光条件下拍摄清晰、色彩丰富的照片。我们希望视频剪辑具有高动态范围、丰富的音频和流畅的图像稳定性。用于超广角和长焦镜头的额外相机是一个优点。考虑专用夜间模式、支持各种视频录制分辨率以及延时拍摄、慢动作等其他照片模式等功能也很重要。</p><h3>电池和软件</h3><p>最后，在电池续航时间方面，我们希望设备能够拥有全天的续航时间，并且在我们的本地视频运行测试中也能取得出色的成绩（一次充电至少 16 小时，但显然越多越好）。在过去的几年里，无线充电功能几乎无处不在，我们的大多数首选产品都具有这种额外的功能。最后，随着人们使用手机的时间比以往任何时候都长，我们希望看到公司承诺至少三年的软件支持、升级和定期安全更新。</p><h2>现在最值得购买的 Android 手机</h2><h2></h2><h2>最佳 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="6c0fc07b5bfe47688db2b2d8968dd3ac" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtUHJvLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtVGVsZXBob3RvL2RwL0IwQkNRV1lSMlo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tbnotMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjhkZTg5YTJkLWIzNDQtNGQyMi1hZTg5LWIzMTRiNzVmY2IxZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZuzv_OntlWKtc3kU_R6DzOAL7wpXaS2FC4opPdWgj1c&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Pro-Smartphone-Telephoto%2Fdp%2FB0BCQWYR2Z">Pixel 7 Pro</a>和标准<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtNy01Ry1BbmRyb2lkLVBob25lL2RwL0IwQkNRWFk1Mlo_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASpA5F4f1KXYW4oQgh_yMRWREBd33uFTYbfquLiIWWVt&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-7-5G-Android-Phone%2Fdp%2FB0BCQXY52Z%3Fth%3D1">Pixel 7</a>可能不是市场上绝对最快的手机，但它们在纯粹性能方面的不足可以通过周到的软件来弥补。得益于谷歌的 Tensor G2 芯片，Pixel 7 系列具有强大的人工智能和机器学习功能，支持设备上语言识别和实时翻译等功能。您还可以获得华丽的 OLED 显示屏以及当今<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html">智能手机中最佳的整体相机质量</a>。标准 Pixel 7 的起价仅为 600 美元，谷歌最新旗舰产品的价值也令人难以置信。两者之间的主要区别在于 Pixel 7 Pro 拥有更大的 6.7 英寸屏幕，并配备第三个后置摄像头，支持 ​​5 倍光学变焦。但无论您喜欢更小还是更大的设备，Pixel 7 或 Pixel 7 Pro 都不会出错。</p><ul><li><p><strong>处理器</strong>：谷歌张量G2</p></li><li><p><strong>显示屏</strong>：6.7 英寸 QHD+，高达 120Hz</p></li><li><p><strong>摄像头</strong>：后置阵列（50MP广角、12MP超广角、48MP长焦）、10.8MP前置摄像头</p></li><li><p><strong>电池</strong>：5,000mAh</p></li></ul><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7-and-pixel-7-pro-review-still-the-best-bargain-in-flagship-phones-170031940.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7 Pro 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳中端Android手机：OnePlus 11 </h2><p><core-commerce id="1013518286f041b7be4c6a83405b2a98" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>对于那些想要一部大屏幕、出色的摄像头和卓越性能的手机，但价格又低于传统旗舰机的人来说， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9PbmVQbHVzLVVubG9ja2VkLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtSGFzc2VsYmxhZC1Qcm9jZXNzb3IvZHAvQjBCTldRQzlGSi8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAX-H-HDCbozJUO5Ri9Pm3mvkdJEw_ZVvcGSOfpg2-wVG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOnePlus-Unlocked-Smartphone-Hasselblad-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0BNWQC9FJ%2F%3Fth%3D1">OnePlus 11</a>在廉价手机和更高端设备之间取得了良好的平衡。在很多方面，OnePlus 11 就像更实惠的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-review-a-solid-phone-thats-probably-not-worth-the-upgrade-173026346.html">Galaxy S23+</a> 。你不仅拥有类似的 6.7 英寸 120Hz 显示屏，还配备快速的 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片和 5,000 mAh 的大电池。与此同时，得益于 OnePlus 强劲的 100 瓦有线充电功能，它的充电速度比任何谷歌或三星手机都快。在相机方面，该公司与哈苏的持续合作显着提高了图像质量。</p><p> OP11的主要缺点是其IP64防尘防水等级低于竞争对手的设备，而且相机的2倍光学变焦镜头感觉有点短。但随着 OnePlus 增加了更广泛的运营商兼容性，并承诺四年的操作系统升级和五年的安全补丁，OP11 是一个装备精良的选择，成本明显低于竞争对手。</p><ul><li><p><strong>处理器</strong>：高通 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2</p></li><li><p><strong>显示屏</strong>：6.7 英寸 QHD+，高达 120Hz</p></li><li><p><strong>摄像头</strong>：后置阵列（50MP主传感器、48MP超广角、32MP长焦）、16MP前置摄像头</p></li><li><p><strong>电池</strong>：5,000mAh</p></li></ul><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-11-review-price-release-date-cameras-150015371.html"><strong>阅读我们对 OnePlus11 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳预算 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7a </h2><p><core-commerce id="8af72094077040eea8d5a86a5802492c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p><p>售价 500 美元的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0b3JlLmdvb2dsZS5jb20vP3BsaT0xJmhsPWVuLVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZGU4OWEyZC1iMzQ0LTRkMjItYWU4OS1iMzE0Yjc1ZmNiMWQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWBJdvYYzyh8qXtdVOgZLQuwiN_d6MKNMXdgavl3iu6b&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.google.com%2F%3Fpli%3D1%26hl%3Den-US">Pixel 7a</a>满足了我们对一款出色、价格实惠的 Android 手机的所有需求（如果您的预算较少，请查看我们<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-cheap-phones-130017793.html">最便宜的手机</a>指南）。新功能包括更快的 Tensor G2 芯片、更流畅的 90Hz 显示屏，以及首次在 Google A 系列手机上支持无线充电。它采用了 IP67 防水等级的全新设计，外观和触感与标准 Pixel 7 相似，但价格便宜 100 美元。得益于五年的安全更新和至少三年的软件更新，您还可以获得大力支持。 Pixel 7a 唯一的缺点相当小，包括缺乏专用变焦镜头以及不支持 mmWave 5G（除非您从 Verizon 购买稍微贵一点的 550 美元型号）。</p><ul><li><p><strong>处理器</strong>：谷歌张量G2</p></li><li><p><strong>显示屏</strong>：6.1 英寸 FHD+，高达 90Hz</p></li><li><p><strong>摄像头</strong>：后置阵列（64MP广角、13MP超广角）、13MP前置摄像头</p></li><li><p><strong>电池</strong>：4,385mAh</p></li></ul><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7a-review-its-got-everything-you-need-and-more-for-just-499-184517525.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7a 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳优质 Android 手机：三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra </h2><p><core-commerce id="a6ef601583384a64973e928e7c0f3c94" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> With a starting price of $1,200, the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVe1eNCu8XYyFXTbnswQHxk2ZNnTC1JBBPVTrU2LLOhQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Factory-Unlocked-Android-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB0BLP2PY6N%2F%3Fth%3D1">Galaxy S23 Ultra</a> is very expensive, but it has excellent performance, a great camera system and practically everything you could ever want or need in a smartphone. Its specs include a huge <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html">6.8-inch OLED display</a> with a 120Hz adaptive refresh rate, a total of five cameras (main, ultra-wide, 3x zoom, 10x zoom and a selfie shooter) and a built-in S Pen stylus for drawing and note-taking. It also features a huge 5,000 mAh battery that delivers some of the longest runtime we&#39;ve seen on any phone. And with Samsung&#39;s renewed commitment to software support, you can expect a minimum of four major OS upgrades and five years of regular security patches.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Processor</strong> : Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2</p></li><li><p> <strong>Display</strong> : 6.8-inch QHD+, up to 120Hz</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cameras</strong> : Rear array (200MP wide, 12MP ultrawide, 10MP telephoto), 12MP front camera</p></li><li><p> <strong>Battery</strong> : 5,000mAh</p></li></ul><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html"><strong>Read our full review of the Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra</strong></a></p><h2> Best foldable Android phone: Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="7912129d0816483492efd7b56884f0ed" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Despite increased competition from the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-fold-review-the-challenger-that-samsung-needs-specs-price-170003458.html">Pixel Fold</a> , for people who want to maximize their mobile productivity, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUd8fwjqgrBUA-1vwQGHgGKNBdbfqKCIkF-kqPPuxlbD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Storage-Unlocked-Smartphone-Streaming%2Fdp%2FB0C63QGGBK" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/SAMSUNG-Storage-Unlocked-Smartphone-Streaming/dp/B0C63QGGBK">the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5</a> is still the best big foldable phone on the market. On the latest model, not only has Samsung added two new gestures for launching into side-by-side multitasking or switching from a full screen to a windowed app, it has also increased the number of recent apps you can see on the taskbar from two to four. The Z Fold 5&#39;s Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 chipset also delivers faster performance than on the Pixel Fold, and even though this Samsung phone has a smaller power cell (4,400 mAh vs 4,800 mAh), it has better battery life, too. But the biggest change for this generation is Samsung&#39;s new Flex Hinge, which allows the phone to close completely flat and makes it thinner to boot. Unfortunately, its camera system is largely unchanged from last year, and with prices starting at $1,800, the Z Fold 5 isn&#39;t even remotely close to being affordable.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Processor</strong> : Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2</p></li><li><p> <strong>Display</strong> : 6.2-inch HD+ front display (up to 120Hz), 7.6-inch QXGA+ main display (up to 120Hz)</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cameras</strong> : Rear array (50MP wide, 12MP ultrawide, 10MP telephoto), 10MP (Cover) + 4MP UDC (Main) front camera</p></li><li><p> <strong>Battery</strong> : 4,400mAh</p></li></ul><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/galaxy-z-fold-5-review-five-years-in-samsung-is-treading-water-140002461.html"><strong>Read our full review of the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5</strong></a></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8de89a2d-b344-4d22-ae89-b314b75fcb1d</guid><dc:creator> Sam Rutherford</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 08 Sep 2023 16:45:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694191506</ingested><modified> 2023-09-08T16:45:23+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/78c254a0-bd23-11ed-bb1f-7eca272d4986" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:desc